  "notes": [
    {
      "title": "FY2025 vs FY2024 — Narrative Evolution Analysis",
      "note_type": null,
      "date": null,
      "quarter": null,
      "tags": [
        "strategy"
      ],
      "rating": 3,
      "active": true,
      "content": "[Narrative Drift]\nIonQ evolved from quantum computing company to 'quantum platform company' across computing, networking, sensing and security. Losses increased substantially ($510.4M vs $331.6M).\n[Red Flags]\n• Algorithmic Qubit metric no longer emphasized\n• Net losses +54% YoY\n• Cash 9x growth likely from acquisitions/financing, not operational improvement\n• New satellite imagery revenue stream may boost top-line without core business improvement",
      "source_doc": null
    },
    {
      "title": "FY2025 10-K Analysis",
      "note_type": null,
      "date": null,
      "quarter": null,
      "tags": [
        "strategy",
        "growth"
      ],
      "rating": 3,
      "active": true,
      "content": "[Financial Performance]\nIonQ in high-growth, pre-profitability phase. Revenue FY2025: $130M (+202% YoY). Net loss: $510.4M. Cash & equivalents grew dramatically from $363.8M to $3,336.8M. Acquisitions: Oxford Ionics, Lightsynq Technologies.\n[Strategic Priorities]\n• Trapped-ion architecture with clearest path to fault-tolerant QC\n• Acquisitions to accelerate roadmap (Electronic Qubit Control, photonic interconnects)\n• Expand quantum ecosystem (networking, sensing, security)\n• Pending SkyWater Technology acquisition for secure quantum foundry\n[Management Tone]\nBullish",
      "source_doc": null
    }
  ],
